  "ai_usage": "This is a copy-paste DESIGN TOKEN foundation, not a visual effect. Lift the :root block into your project. Use the TWO-TIER pattern: primitives (--blue-500) hold raw values; semantic tokens (--color-primary: var(--blue-500)) express intent and are what components reference. Never hardcode hex in components — reference semantic tokens so themes/dark-mode swap cleanly. Verify contrast for every text/bg pairing you introduce.",
  "path": "effects/color-systems/semantic-color-tokens.html",
  "source": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n  <title>Semantic Color Tokens</title>\n  <script type=\"application/json\" id=\"effect-meta\">\n  {\n    \"id\": \"semantic-color-tokens\",\n    \"title\": \"Semantic Color Tokens\",\n    \"summary\": \"A two-tier color token system (primitive scale → semantic roles) as copy-ready CSS custom properties.\",\n    \"description\": \"A reference specimen, not an animation: defines a primitive color scale (--blue-50…900 etc.) and maps it to semantic roles (--color-bg, --color-text, --color-primary, --color-danger…). This is the backbone of a themeable design system.\",\n    \"theme\": \"color-systems\",\n    \"categories\": [\"design-tokens\", \"color\", \"theming\", \"reference\"],\n    \"tags\": [\"tokens\", \"design-system\", \"palette\", \"semantic\", \"css-variables\", \"theming\"],\n    \"tech\": [\"css\"],\n    \"era\": \"2020s\",\n    \"difficulty\": \"beginner\",\n    \"dependencies\": [],\n    \"browser_support\": \"All browsers (CSS custom properties).\",\n    \"performance_notes\": \"Variables only; no runtime cost.\",\n    \"accessibility_notes\": \"Token pairs are chosen for WCAG contrast (text-on-bg, text-on-primary). When adding tokens, verify contrast ratios (>=4.5:1 for body text).\",\n    \"customization\": [\n      { \"name\": \"primitive scale\", \"description\": \"Raw hues with numeric steps (50-900)\", \"default\": \"see :root\" },\n      { \"name\": \"semantic roles\", \"description\": \"Intent-named vars mapping to primitives\", \"default\": \"see :root\" }\n    ],\n    \"variations\": [\"Add a [data-theme=light] override block\", \"Extend with success/warning/info roles\", \"Generate the scale with oklch() for perceptual uniformity\"],\n    \"related\": [\"gradient-library\", \"dark-mode-tokens\", \"type-scale\"],\n    \"ai_usage\": \"This is a copy-paste DESIGN TOKEN foundation, not a visual effect. Lift the :root block into your project. Use the TWO-TIER pattern: primitives (--blue-500) hold raw values; semantic tokens (--color-primary: var(--blue-500)) express intent and are what components reference. Never hardcode hex in components — reference semantic tokens so themes/dark-mode swap cleanly. Verify contrast for every text/bg pairing you introduce.\"\n  }\n  </script>\n  <style>\n    :root {\n      /* primitives */\n      --gray-50:#f8fafc; --gray-100:#eef1f6; --gray-300:#cbd3e1; --gray-500:#64748b; --gray-700:#334155; --gray-900:#0f172a;\n      --violet-300:#c4b5fd; --violet-500:#7c5cff; --violet-700:#5b3ee0;\n      --teal-500:#2dd4bf; --red-500:#ef4444; --amber-500:#f59e0b; --green-500:#22c55e;\n      /* semantic roles (dark theme) */\n      --color-bg: var(--gray-900); --color-surface:#151925; --color-border:#262c3d;\n      --color-text: var(--gray-50); --color-text-muted: var(--gray-500);\n      --color-primary: var(--violet-500); --color-primary-text:#fff;\n      --color-danger: var(--red-500); --color-warning: var(--amber-500); --color-success: var(--green-500);\n    }\n    * { box-sizing: border-box; }\n    html, body { margin: 0; height: 100%; }\n    body { background: var(--color-bg); color: var(--color-text); font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; padding: 1.2rem; overflow:auto; }\n    h2 { margin: 0 0 1rem; font-size: 1.1rem; }\n    .group { font-size: .7rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .08em; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin: 1rem 0 .4rem; }\n    .swatches { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(120px,1fr)); gap: .5rem; }\n    .sw { border-radius: 10px; padding: .7rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); font-size: .72rem; }\n    .sw b { display: block; font-size: .8rem; }\n    .chip { height: 26px; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: .4rem; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.1); }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h2>Semantic tokens (dark theme)</h2>\n  <div class=\"swatches\">\n    <div class=\"sw\"><div class=\"chip\" style=\"background:var(--color-bg)\"></div><b>bg</b>gray-900</div>\n    <div class=\"sw\"><div class=\"chip\" style=\"background:var(--color-surface)\"></div><b>surface</b></div>\n    <div class=\"sw\"><div class=\"chip\" style=\"background:var(--color-primary)\"></div><b>primary</b>violet-500</div>\n    <div class=\"sw\"><div class=\"chip\" style=\"background:var(--color-success)\"></div><b>success</b></div>\n    <div class=\"sw\"><div class=\"chip\" style=\"background:var(--color-warning)\"></div><b>warning</b></div>\n    <div class=\"sw\"><div class=\"chip\" style=\"background:var(--color-danger)\"></div><b>danger</b></div>\n  </div>\n  <p class=\"group\">Primitive scale (excerpt)</p>\n  <div class=\"swatches\">\n    <div class=\"sw\"><div class=\"chip\" style=\"background:var(--violet-300)\"></div><b>violet-300</b></div>\n    <div class=\"sw\"><div class=\"chip\" style=\"background:var(--violet-500)\"></div><b>violet-500</b></div>\n    <div class=\"sw\"><div class=\"chip\" style=\"background:var(--violet-700)\"></div><b>violet-700</b></div>\n    <div class=\"sw\"><div class=\"chip\" style=\"background:var(--teal-500)\"></div><b>teal-500</b></div>\n  </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n"
}
